    <item>
      <title>WSL: Real Linux Inside Your Windows</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/articles/wsl-resources-from-linux-on-windows/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/articles/wsl-resources-from-linux-on-windows/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;🎥 This article has a companion video on my &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/@ropizzolato&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;YouTube channel&lt;/a&gt; (in Portuguese). The video link will be added here once it&amp;rsquo;s published.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;!-- When the video is published, replace the line above with: {{&lt; youtube VIDEO_ID &gt;}} --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)&lt;/strong&gt; is a Windows 10/11 feature that lets you use real Linux resources directly from Windows, officially supported by Microsoft. It&amp;rsquo;s not new, but it remains one of the most practical ways to study and work with Linux — no dual-boot, no hypervisor setup. If you&amp;rsquo;re an IT student getting started, this is probably the simplest entry point.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is WSL?&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;what-is-wsl&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#what-is-wsl&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;WSL is a compatibility layer that runs &lt;strong&gt;real Linux&lt;/strong&gt; inside Windows. It&amp;rsquo;s not traditional emulation or a classic virtual machine — although under the hood WSL2 uses lightweight virtualization via Hyper-V.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WSL is currently at &lt;strong&gt;version 2&lt;/strong&gt;. Version 1, simpler and less compatible, is nearly obsolete — avoid it. WSL2 advantages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real Linux kernel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Near-total compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Better performance in many scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lightweight virtualization (via Hyper-V)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What can you do with WSL?&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;what-can-you-do-with-wsl&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#what-can-you-do-with-wsl&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A lot: run &lt;code&gt;bash&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ssh&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt;, and other tools; use package managers like &lt;code&gt;apt&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;yum&lt;/code&gt;; run Python, Node, Go, Docker, and Git; compile code; automate tasks; access Linux servers. For many professionals, WSL has completely replaced dual-boot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A huge differentiator is the &lt;strong&gt;Windows integration&lt;/strong&gt;: you can reach your &lt;code&gt;C:\&lt;/code&gt; drive through the &lt;code&gt;/mnt/c&lt;/code&gt; mount point, run Linux commands from PowerShell (and Windows commands from inside Linux), and integrate with VS Code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Limitations and caveats&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;limitations-and-caveats&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#limitations-and-caveats&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;WSL is &lt;strong&gt;not a replacement for a production Linux server&lt;/strong&gt; — I/O performance can vary a lot.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Watch out for security: handle sensitive files with care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not every corporate environment allows WSL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where I recommend it: study environments, development, task automation, and hybrid setups — when you natively live on Windows but still need Linux.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Installing WSL2&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;installing-wsl2&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#installing-wsl2&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The official documentation is at &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;learn.microsoft.com/windows/wsl/install&lt;/a&gt;. Prerequisites: Windows 10 version 2004+ (build 19041+) or Windows 11 — the most common case today, since Windows 10 support ended in October 2025.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open &lt;strong&gt;PowerShell as administrator&lt;/strong&gt; and run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-install&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wait for it to finish, then verify the installed version:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-version&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Managing distributions&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;managing-distributions&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#managing-distributions&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;List what&amp;rsquo;s installed and what&amp;rsquo;s available online:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-list&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-verbose&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-list&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-online&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ll install Ubuntu 24.04 (an LTS release, with extended support) and also Fedora 43:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;Ubuntu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mf&#34;&gt;24.04&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;FedoraLinux&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mf&#34;&gt;43&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After each install, set a username and password. To confirm you&amp;rsquo;re on real Linux:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;cat /etc/os-release&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To leave WSL and return to PowerShell, type &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other useful commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-list&lt;/span&gt;                       &lt;span class=&#34;c&#34;&gt;# list installed distros&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-unregister&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;DistroName&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c&#34;&gt;# remove a distro&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-setdefault&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;Ubuntu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mf&#34;&gt;24.04&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c&#34;&gt;# set the default distro (or -s)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;root&lt;/span&gt;                      &lt;span class=&#34;c&#34;&gt;# log in as root (handy to reset a password with passwd)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-help&lt;/span&gt;                       &lt;span class=&#34;c&#34;&gt;# all options&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you&amp;rsquo;re inside your distro, the first thing I suggest is updating the system:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt update &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; sudo apt upgrade&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/code&gt; chains commands: the second one only runs if the first succeeds (return code 0). You can check the last command&amp;rsquo;s return code with &lt;code&gt;echo $?&lt;/code&gt; — try &lt;code&gt;ls&lt;/code&gt; on a non-existent path and watch it change to 2. &lt;code&gt;man ls&lt;/code&gt; documents the &lt;em&gt;Exit Status&lt;/em&gt; values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The two file systems&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;the-two-file-systems&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#the-two-file-systems&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the most important concept for using WSL well:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
	&lt;thead&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;th&gt;Path&lt;/th&gt;
					&lt;th&gt;File system&lt;/th&gt;
					&lt;th&gt;What it is&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/thead&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;/mnt/c/...&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;NTFS (Windows)&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;Your &lt;code&gt;C:\&lt;/code&gt; drive, mounted inside Linux&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;/home/&amp;lt;user&amp;gt;/...&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;ext4 (Linux)&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;Virtual disk managed by WSL&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;\\wsl$\&amp;lt;Distro&amp;gt;\...&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;ext4 (Linux)&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;A bridge for Windows to reach the Linux filesystem&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The path &lt;code&gt;C:\Users\&amp;lt;User&amp;gt;\Project&lt;/code&gt; is equivalent to &lt;code&gt;/mnt/c/Users/&amp;lt;User&amp;gt;/Project&lt;/code&gt; — same files. Meanwhile &lt;code&gt;/home/&amp;lt;user&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; lives on an ext4 virtual disk that isn&amp;rsquo;t directly on NTFS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Try it yourself: inside WSL, run &lt;code&gt;cd /mnt/c/&lt;/code&gt;, create a folder with &lt;code&gt;mkdir&lt;/code&gt; and a file with &lt;code&gt;touch&lt;/code&gt;, then check Windows File Explorer — they&amp;rsquo;re there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important tip:&lt;/strong&gt; for development environments, avoid working under &lt;code&gt;/mnt/c&lt;/code&gt; — keep your projects in your user&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;/home&lt;/code&gt;, where performance is much better.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Windows and VS Code integration&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;windows-and-vs-code-integration&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#windows-and-vs-code-integration&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;From inside your &lt;code&gt;/home&lt;/code&gt;, you can call Windows programs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;explorer.exe .   &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# opens File Explorer in the current folder&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;code .           &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# opens VS Code in the current folder (via the WSL extension)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trailing dot means the current directory (use &lt;code&gt;pwd&lt;/code&gt; to see where you are). In VS Code, install the official Microsoft &lt;strong&gt;WSL&lt;/strong&gt; extension if it doesn&amp;rsquo;t open in remote mode automatically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s test something that only works on Linux. Create a &lt;code&gt;wsl&lt;/code&gt; folder, and inside it a &lt;code&gt;hello.sh&lt;/code&gt; file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cp&#34;&gt;#!/bin/bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hello from Linux via WSL&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;date
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;uname -a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make it executable and run it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;chmod +x hello.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;./hello.sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;uname -a&lt;/code&gt; prints system information — including the real Linux kernel running inside Windows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Cross-OS commands&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;cross-os-commands&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#cross-os-commands&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can mix both worlds. In &lt;strong&gt;PowerShell&lt;/strong&gt;, running a Linux command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;ipconfig&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;grep&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;ipv4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;ipconfig&lt;/code&gt; is native to Windows; &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt; filters the output on Linux (&lt;code&gt;-i&lt;/code&gt; makes it case-insensitive). A plain &lt;code&gt;wsl ls&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code&gt;dir&lt;/code&gt; works too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The reverse also works — Windows commands &lt;strong&gt;inside WSL&lt;/strong&gt; (don&amp;rsquo;t forget the &lt;code&gt;.exe&lt;/code&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;notepad.exe .wslconfig
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ls -la &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; findstr.exe &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;search_term&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember: to run a Linux tool from PowerShell, it must be installed in the distro. On Ubuntu/Debian, check with &lt;code&gt;dpkg -l | grep &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; and install with &lt;code&gt;apt install&lt;/code&gt;. On Fedora/Red Hat, use &lt;code&gt;rpm -qa | grep &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;yum install&lt;/code&gt;. A classic example: &lt;code&gt;ifconfig&lt;/code&gt; (legacy, replaced by the &lt;code&gt;ip&lt;/code&gt; command) requires the &lt;code&gt;net-tools&lt;/code&gt; package:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt install net-tools -y    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Ubuntu/Debian&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo yum install net-tools -y    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Fedora/Red Hat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;-y&lt;/code&gt; flag answers &amp;ldquo;yes&amp;rdquo; automatically to the package manager&amp;rsquo;s prompt. Worth noting: &lt;code&gt;apt&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;yum&lt;/code&gt; resolve dependencies automatically — unlike raw &lt;code&gt;dpkg&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;rpm&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Limiting resources with .wslconfig&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;limiting-resources-with-wslconfig&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#limiting-resources-with-wslconfig&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;WSL loves to consume resources — it&amp;rsquo;s like Chrome devouring RAM. Without limits, it keeps eating memory until your system starts caching to disk and slows down. The fix is the &lt;code&gt;.wslconfig&lt;/code&gt; file at &lt;code&gt;%UserProfile%\.wslconfig&lt;/code&gt; (that is, &lt;code&gt;C:\Users\&amp;lt;your_user&amp;gt;\.wslconfig&lt;/code&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ini&#34; data-lang=&#34;ini&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;[wsl2]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;memory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;4GB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;processors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;swap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;2GB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;swapFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;C:\\wsl\\swap.vhdx&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;localhostForwarding&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;memory&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;processors&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;swap&lt;/code&gt; cap WSL2&amp;rsquo;s global usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;swapFile&lt;/code&gt; sets where the swap file lives (the backslash is doubled because it&amp;rsquo;s an escape character). Without it, the default is &lt;code&gt;%UserProfile%\AppData\Local\Temp\swap.vhdx&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;localhostForwarding=true&lt;/code&gt; is great for exposing applications — for example, &lt;code&gt;python3 -m http.server 8000&lt;/code&gt; inside WSL, then open &lt;code&gt;localhost:8000&lt;/code&gt; in a Windows browser.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/wsl-config&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;full list of settings is in the official docs&lt;/a&gt;. You can also set limits &lt;strong&gt;per distro&lt;/strong&gt;, but that&amp;rsquo;s a topic for another article.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Shutting down WSL&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;shutting-down-wsl&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#shutting-down-wsl&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A good practice is shutting WSL down when you&amp;rsquo;re done, freeing memory and CPU:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wsl&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-shutdown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In rare cases the process insists on staying alive. If that happens, force-kill it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;taskkill&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;im&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;wslservice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;exe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Copy code&#34;
    data-copied-label=&#34;Copied!&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;/f&lt;/code&gt; forces termination and &lt;code&gt;/im&lt;/code&gt; targets the process by name (you can use &lt;code&gt;/pid&lt;/code&gt; as well).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Conclusion&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#conclusion&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;WSL has many more features — this article is the foundation for upcoming content on WSL, Linux, and systems administration. If you have questions or topic suggestions, find me on &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/@ropizzolato&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;YouTube&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/rpizzolato&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=&#34;https://linkedin.com/in/rpizzolato&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

